cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NA

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and denoising. The use of diffusion maps and graph filtering also suggests that it could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves alignment and classification of images, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of matrices and eigenvalues/eigenvectors suggests that it could be related to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
